Person A opens an event to edit it.  Then the phone rings and they get into a five-minute conversation while the edit dialogue box is open.  Meanwhile, person B opens the same event in edit mode.  **problem - this is allowed**.  Person B makes their changes and saves the event.  They refresh their browser and see that the changes are there, so they leave happy.  Person A hangs up the phone and finally makes their changes to the event.  They save it successfully, and by doing so, clobber the changes made by person B.  Person B is very unhappy because now their changes have disappeared, and is grumpy for the rest of the day, much to the chagrin of their co-workers.

(Again, apologies if this has been fixed in subsequent releases - hope so, because then it's a great argument to upgrade)

